content:
Enable Null Measure Handling in Orgs Created Before Spring '17

Use null measure handling to specify null as the default value for numeric columns in your recipes, dataflows, and CSV uploads. When another default value isn’t specified for a numeric column and null measure handling is enabled, CRM Analytics replaces a blank with a null value.

If CRM Analytics was initially set up in your org before Spring ’17, contact Salesforce Customer Support.

To enable null measure handling: Customize Application

After enabling null measure handling, review your dataflows and take these steps as needed:

* Update your dataflow definition files to use null instead of 0 in the defaultValue attributes for measure fields.
* Create instances of long-lived datasets used as a source for dataflows using a null defaultValue for measure fields.
* Reimplement delta transformations in your dataflows using computeRelative and computeExpression transformations.

The delta transformation isn’t supported when null measure handling is enabled. Dataflows containing delta transformations fail.
title: Enable Null Measure Handling in CRM Analytics
